Resident Evil: Damnation Review

Resident Evil: Damnation is a Japanese animated action horror film that takes place in the universe of the Resident Evil video game franchise. The movie follows Leon S Kennedy, a special agent for the US government, as he is sent to a fictional Eastern European country called "Eastern Slav Republic" to investigate the use of bio-organic weapons in the country's civil war. Leon soon discovers new strains of the T-Virus, alongside corrupt government officials and genetically engineered BOWs that threaten to spread the virus across the globe. The movie features impressive animation, thrilling action scenes, and a suspenseful storyline that keeps the viewers engaged throughout. Moreover, the characters are well-developed and the voice acting is top-notch, with Matthew Mercer's performance as Leon being a particular standout. Overall, Resident Evil: Damnation is a must-watch for fans of the Resident Evil franchise and action-horror movies in general.

TRIVIA AND POPULAR DIALOGUES

Trivia

This is the first Resident Evil release not to mention or reference the Umbrella Corporation.

This was Robin Sachs' final film before his death on February 1, 2013 at the age of 61.
